  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\nhardhat-chai-matchers 2.0.3 / hardhat-ethers 3.0.5\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nThe (not) `reverted` matcher throws an error when calling a `view` function returning `bytes32` that does not revert.\r\n\r\nThis is because the code inside `expect` actually returns a string, and `reverted.ts` interprets that return value as a hash. Then, when it tries to get the transaction receipt it fails at [this line](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/%40nomicfoundation/hardhat-chai-matchers%402.0.3/packages/hardhat-chai-matchers/src/internal/reverted/reverted.ts#L37).\r\n\r\nTested with latest tag `2.0.3`. Probably also happens with other types that can be interpreted as a hash?\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nSuppose I have library with a view function that doesn't revert, but returns `bytes32`:\r\n\r\nSolidity:\r\n```\r\ncontract Test {\r\n    bytes32 private _value;\r\n\r\n    function setValue(bytes32 value) external {\r\n        _value = value;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function getValueBytes32() external view returns (bytes32) {\r\n        return _value;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function getValueUint() external view returns (uint256) {\r\n        return uint256(_value);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nTest:\r\n\r\n```\r\nit('is ok', async () => {\r\n    await expect(test.getValueUint()).not.to.be.reverted;\r\n});\r\n\r\nit('throws', async () => {\r\n    await expect(test.getValueBytes32()).not.to.be.reverted;\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error in the second scenario is:\r\n```\r\nHardhatChaiMatchersAssertionError: Assertion error: receipt should not be null\r\n```\r\n\r\nA simple workaround is to just not use `expect` in these cases:\r\n\r\n```\r\nit('is ok as a workaround', async () => {\r\n    await test.getValueBytes32(); // does not revert\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut ideally `not.reverted` should work as with non-view functions and the other return values.\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\nchai-matchers, not.to.be.reverted",
